JUDGES: Javier Borrego Borrego;Karel Jungwiert;Mark Villiger;Peer Lorenzen;Rait Maruste;Renate Jaeger;Snejana Botoucharova
TEXT: The applicant , Mr PERSON , is a NORP national who was born in DATE and lives in PERSON . ORG ( “ the Government ” ) were represented by their Agent , Mr PERSON , from ORG .
The facts of the case , as submitted by the parties , may be summarised as follows .
According to the Government , on DATE the applicant sued a certain ORG in LOC ( okresní soud ) .
On DATE ORG granted the applicant ’s action ordering ORG to pay CZK CARDINAL,CARDINAL ( EUR CARDINAL ) to the applicant .
According to the applicant , as ORG had not paid the sum at issue , he requested ORG , in DATE , to execute the judgment . Apparently , the execution proceedings have not yet been terminated .
In his application form , the applicant submitted that in DATE , he had brought an action for damages against a certain GPE
The Government denied that such an action had been filed .

In his observations in reply , the applicant said that he had filed a criminal complaint against GPE at FAC ( PERSON – město ) which subsequently instituted criminal proceedings against GPE ’s accomplice .

The relevant domestic law and practice concerning remedies for the excessive length of judicial proceedings are stated in the ORG ’s decision in the case of PERSON v. GPE , no . MONEY ( dec . ) , § § CARDINAL - CARDINAL , DATE ) .
